07:19.310 --> 07:21.610
Fonz, we've got
to see you.

07:21.610 --> 07:24.610
This isn't happening.

07:24.610 --> 07:26.110
(moaning)

07:26.110 --> 07:27.610
(French accent):
Oh, don't leave,
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">mon cher{\r}.</font></font></i>

07:27.610 --> 07:29.620
Hey, yeah, we'll
share, we'll share.

07:29.620 --> 07:31.120
You just sit tight.

07:31.120 --> 07:33.120
Memorize some American
words, will you?

07:33.120 --> 07:34.040
Get over here.

07:34.040 --> 07:36.490
Malph... will you
get over here, Malph?

07:36.490 --> 07:37.990
Find your own.

07:37.990 --> 07:38.990
Right, Fonz.

07:38.990 --> 07:40.290
What are you doing here?

07:40.290 --> 07:42.080
Well, Fonz, we've
got a problem.
Yeah.

07:42.080 --> 07:43.910
Your mother told
you where I was?

07:43.910 --> 07:45.800
Yeah, she did, but she
wouldn't have, Fonz,

07:45.800 --> 07:47.300
not if it wasn't
a big emergency.

07:47.300 --> 07:48.670
Yeah, Fonz,
an emergency.

07:48.670 --> 07:50.420
What are you,
a parrot?

07:50.420 --> 07:51.840
Yeah, you see, we...

07:51.840 --> 07:53.310
we've got to play
this bar mitzvah,

07:53.310 --> 07:55.260
and the address is locked
up in your garage.

07:55.260 --> 07:57.180
And Malph
doesn't know

07:57.640 --> 07:59.680
where the place
is, <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">correcto{\r}?</font></font></i>

07:59.680 --> 08:01.680
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Correcto, Fonz.
Fabbo{\r}.</font></font></i>

08:01.680 --> 08:03.350
I got it!
There he goes again.

08:03.350 --> 08:05.350
The name
of the place is Beth.

08:05.350 --> 08:06.350
I knew it
was a girl's name.

08:06.850 --> 08:07.690
Beth Israel.

08:09.520 --> 08:11.490
Come on, let's hurry up,
we don't want to be late.

08:11.490 --> 08:14.490
Right... see you,
Fonz, have fun.

08:14.490 --> 08:15.500
Fonz?

08:16.000 --> 08:17.000
Yeah?

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
I was gonna ask you
what you're doing here,

08:19.000 --> 08:21.000
but, uh, I
can tell.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.000
Yeah, I bet you can,
and so can your mother.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.510
Oh, uh, don't blame that
on her, Fonz, really.

08:25.510 --> 08:27.010
Don't you have
someplace to go?

08:27.010 --> 08:28.010
Yeah, yeah.
Yeah.

08:28.010 --> 08:29.290
Fonz?
Yeah?

08:29.290 --> 08:31.090
What are you studying?

08:31.090 --> 08:32.549
Foreign Relations?

08:32.549 --> 08:34.010
(chuckling)

08:36.470 --> 08:37.970
Where was I?

08:37.970 --> 08:39.970
Now, they don't know
this yet, you see,

08:39.970 --> 08:40.970
but those
are my pals,

08:40.970 --> 08:43.470
and I'm going to
graduate with them, huh?

08:43.470 --> 08:45.980
Uh... "graduate"?

08:46.480 --> 08:47.980
Yeah, you know...

08:49.980 --> 08:50.980
Graduate.

08:52.980 --> 08:54.980
(giggles):
Oh, Fonzie.

08:54.980 --> 08:56.400
Hey...

08:56.400 --> 08:57.790
I don't know if
she understands,

08:57.790 --> 09:00.790
but then, I know I
don't care, you know?

09:00.790 --> 09:03.380
MARION:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">You raised money by playing
at the bar mitzva{\r}h</font></font></i>

09:03.880 --> 09:05.380
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">so you could rent your own tux{\r},</font></font></i>

09:05.880 --> 09:08.830
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and now you'll be the
handsomest boy at prom{\r}.</font></font></i>

09:08.830 --> 09:10.800
I don't want to be
late to my own prom.

09:11.300 --> 09:12.300
Now, when you get there,
be sure

09:12.800 --> 09:15.300
to stand up straight
so your cummerbund won't sag.

09:15.300 --> 09:16.810
I-I will, Mom.

09:16.810 --> 09:18.810
Well, I got
to get going.

09:18.810 --> 09:20.810
I want to pick up
Arlene a little early.

09:20.810 --> 09:23.810
Her parents want to take
some home movies of us.

09:24.310 --> 09:25.230
(mimicking James Stewart):
I, uh...

09:25.230 --> 09:28.230
I was thinking I might do my
Jimmy Stewart impression.

09:31.490 --> 09:32.990
That's so good.

09:32.990 --> 09:34.490
Yeah, thanks,
Mom, I like it.

09:34.490 --> 09:37.490
Oh, uh, Richard, the boys
haven't said anything

09:37.990 --> 09:39.780
about, uh, Fonzie
going to school?

09:39.780 --> 09:41.950
No, Mom, of course not,
we can keep a secret.

09:41.950 --> 09:42.830
Oh, good, I'm so glad,

09:43.330 --> 09:44.200
'cause I was worried
about that.

09:44.200 --> 09:45.590
Well, you don't
have to worry.

09:45.590 --> 09:47.540
Good.

09:47.540 --> 09:49.590
Oh, well, here
it comes.

09:49.590 --> 09:51.590
She's gonna tell
me I look like

09:51.590 --> 09:54.010
Casper the Friendly
Ghost or Guy Lombardo

09:54.010 --> 09:56.100
or, uh, the
Good Humor Man

09:56.100 --> 09:57.050
or somebody like
that, right?

09:57.050 --> 10:00.850
Not at all, Rich, I think you
look very handsome.

10:00.850 --> 10:02.640
Oh, now, that's nice.

10:02.640 --> 10:05.100
(mimicking James Stewart):
Wow, uh, thank you
there, Joanie.

10:08.060 --> 10:10.860
You know, he did look like
Casper the Friendly Ghost.

10:10.860 --> 10:12.650
He did not.

10:12.650 --> 10:13.650
Mom, did you
hear the news?

10:13.650 --> 10:15.650
Fonzie's going
to night school.
No!

10:15.650 --> 10:17.620
Oh, where did
you hear that?

10:17.620 --> 10:19.570
I heard it
from Jenny Piccalo.

