♪ A bright uniform ♪

10:44.510 --> 10:48.510
♪ Oh, I love a parade ♪

10:48.510 --> 10:51.020
♪ Hey, hey! ♪

10:51.020 --> 10:54.020
(saxophone solo)

11:03.860 --> 11:06.780
Oh, I'm so happy
to be here with you, Richie.

11:06.780 --> 11:08.780
Oh.
I love my corsage.

11:08.780 --> 11:11.290
Well, I... if you
like this prom,

11:11.790 --> 11:14.790
wait till you see what I've
got planned afterwards.

11:14.790 --> 11:18.290
We're gonna watch the
sunrise together.

11:18.290 --> 11:21.800
♪ I found my thrill... ♪

11:23.430 --> 11:25.720
Later, later.
All right.

11:25.720 --> 11:29.020
GIRL:
I'm not wearing this
corsage, Ralph.

11:29.020 --> 11:30.520
It looks great, Kim.

11:39.400 --> 11:41.730
I don't think it
goes with my dress.

11:42.230 --> 11:43.740
Fussy, fussy.

11:44.240 --> 11:45.240
Look, Kim, it's fresh.

11:45.240 --> 11:46.740
It's the freshest
corsage here.

11:46.740 --> 11:48.240
Ralph's father
has them growing

11:48.240 --> 11:49.740
all over the
backyard.

11:49.740 --> 11:51.210
What do you want?

11:51.210 --> 11:52.710
Anybody can buy
a corsage.

11:52.710 --> 11:54.210
I gave it
the personal touch.

11:54.210 --> 11:55.720
I ripped it
right out of the ground

11:55.720 --> 11:56.630
with my own two hands.

11:58.050 --> 12:00.550
Couldn't you cut off
the roots?

12:00.550 --> 12:03.060
Let's go say hello
to Arlene and Rich.

12:03.060 --> 12:04.560
Hey, uh, Rich, hey,
Arlene, how you doing?

12:04.560 --> 12:06.060
(all saying hello)

12:06.060 --> 12:07.890
Hey, come on,
let's dance.

12:07.890 --> 12:11.600
(band playing "Heart and Soul")

12:11.600 --> 12:15.070
Oh, Kim, I love it
when you hum in my ear.

12:15.070 --> 12:19.070
I'm not humming, there's
a bee in my corsage.

12:25.580 --> 12:28.410
("Heart and Soul" continues)

12:36.120 --> 12:39.630
(song ends)

12:39.630 --> 12:41.930
(applause)

12:41.930 --> 12:44.100
Thank you, thank you.

12:44.100 --> 12:46.930
We hope you're all
enjoying the prom,

12:46.930 --> 12:51.440
coming to you from
Jefferson's ballroom gymnasium,

12:51.440 --> 12:54.310
just a stone's throw
from Arnold's Drive-In.

12:55.720 --> 12:57.730
Now I take great pleasure

12:57.730 --> 13:00.200
to bring on
a very special guest...

13:00.200 --> 13:01.700
(drumroll)

13:01.700 --> 13:03.150
Arthur Fonzarelli!

13:03.150 --> 13:05.120
(cheering, applause)

13:05.120 --> 13:07.120
(band playing
"For He's A Jolly Good Fellow")

13:10.540 --> 13:11.960
FONZIE:
Hi, guys.

13:11.960 --> 13:14.460
Hello, Mr. C.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.380
(music stops)

13:17.300 --> 13:18.630
Hello, Arthur.

13:20.470 --> 13:22.470
Come on, stoolie,
I'll buy you a drink.

13:25.470 --> 13:26.470
All right now, Michelle,

13:26.970 --> 13:30.480
I want you to stand
right there.

13:30.480 --> 13:32.810
Right.

13:32.810 --> 13:34.100
All right.

13:34.100 --> 13:36.100
Listen, uh, before we start
the festivities,

13:36.100 --> 13:38.600
I just want to clear the air
about something.

13:38.600 --> 13:41.600
A lot of you have speculated on
why I'm going to night school.

13:41.600 --> 13:43.110
POTSIE:
Yeah.
(chuckles)

13:43.110 --> 13:45.520
Some of you have said that
I-I'm studying to be a teacher.

13:45.520 --> 13:46.860
(crowd murmurs)
That was
going around.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.360
Wrong.

13:48.360 --> 13:50.860
Some of you said that I was
trying to pick up chicks.

13:50.860 --> 13:51.860
(crowd murmurs)

13:51.860 --> 13:53.870
Wrong.

13:53.870 --> 13:56.370
Somebody even said
that I was studying

13:56.370 --> 13:58.370
to get the Nobel Peace Prize.

13:58.370 --> 14:00.620
That was mine.

14:00.620 --> 14:04.430
All very reasonable
possibilities,

14:04.430 --> 14:06.430
all of them incorrect-o.

14:08.210 --> 14:10.020
Now, you see, I wanted
this to be a surprise.

14:10.520 --> 14:13.940
I didn't realize that
certain people had loose lips.

14:16.890 --> 14:20.890
All right, now the fact is
that tonight,

14:20.890 --> 14:23.900
I join you...

14:23.900 --> 14:26.780
as a graduating senior.

14:26.780 --> 14:29.030
(cheering, applause)

14:35.570 --> 14:37.040
I know you're proud;
I'm proud, too.

14:38.410 --> 14:41.830
Now, the thing is that, uh,
I will be available tonight

14:41.830 --> 14:43.750
to sign all your
yearbooks, all right?

14:43.750 --> 14:44.670
Have a good time.

14:45.170 --> 14:45.670
All right.

14:46.170 --> 14:46.670
(band plays riff)

14:47.140 --> 14:47.920
Thank you, Fonzie.

14:51.340 --> 14:53.840
Oh, excuse me, Fonzie.

14:54.340 --> 14:55.140
This girl was

14:55.140 --> 14:57.850
just stung by a bee.

14:57.850 --> 14:59.900
Well, I think you'd better
go to the ladies' room,

14:59.900 --> 15:00.900
put some mud on it.

15:00.900 --> 15:01.770
Mud is good.

15:01.770 --> 15:03.690
I be right back.

15:03.690 --> 15:05.650
You do that.

15:09.190 --> 15:11.660
Arthur, I don't
have loose lips.

15:11.660 --> 15:14.030
No, Mom, I-I don't think that
he was talking about you.

15:14.030 --> 15:16.700
If the lip fits, wear it.

15:19.500 --> 15:22.000
Yeah, well, he-he didn't
mean it that way.

15:22.000 --> 15:23.460
I know what he meant.

15:23.460 --> 15:24.960
(band playing slow waltz)

15:24.960 --> 15:25.960
You know, Fonzie,

15:25.960 --> 15:27.960
I don't blame you
for being upset

15:27.960 --> 15:30.960
at the way Marion was
shooting off her big mouth.

15:33.300 --> 15:36.270
But also, I'd like
to remind you,

15:36.270 --> 15:38.770
she does do
some nice things, too.

15:38.770 --> 15:40.770
You know, she gets up
early in the morning,

15:40.770 --> 15:42.780
and she makes your breakfast.

15:42.780 --> 15:44.780
She fills your little
thermos bottle

15:45.280 --> 15:46.650
and cooks your vegetables.

15:46.650 --> 15:47.980
Well, I'll tell
you one thing,

15:48.480 --> 15:50.320
she's very good with my
veggies, that's true.

15:50.320 --> 15:54.150
And I think that there comes
a time in everyone's life

15:54.150 --> 15:56.660
when they make at least
one mistake, you know?

15:59.630 --> 16:03.630
Uh, Michelle, would you,
uh, care to dance with me?

16:04.130 --> 16:06.000
Yeah.

16:36.110 --> 16:38.610
You want to dance?

16:38.610 --> 16:40.620
Whoa!

16:58.520 --> 17:00.520
(band playing lively swing tune)

17:27.160 --> 17:29.550
♪ ♪

17:35.000 --> 17:35.890
(music stops)

17:35.890 --> 17:38.760
Yeah!
(cheering, applause)

17:41.730 --> 17:42.730
(chuckles):
Oh.

17:42.730 --> 17:44.010
Thank you, thank you.

17:44.010 --> 17:46.820
We now have
a very special treat.

17:46.820 --> 17:50.820
Our own Potsie Weber
is going to dedicate a song

17:50.820 --> 17:55.110
to his fellow seniors
and to a very special girl.

17:55.110 --> 17:57.940
Potsie will sing "Deeply."

17:57.940 --> 17:58.940
All right!
(applause)

17:58.940 --> 17:59.910
Get those lights down.

18:01.860 --> 18:04.750
Why don't you all come on up
to the bandstand, hold hands.

18:04.750 --> 18:06.670
(band playing "Deeply")

18:14.930 --> 18:18.430
♪ You ask is my love real ♪

18:18.430 --> 18:22.940
♪ All I can say is how I feel ♪

18:22.940 --> 18:24.940
♪ Deeply ♪

18:25.890 --> 18:29.890
♪ Deeply as can be ♪

18:32.900 --> 18:36.400
♪ You seem to need to know ♪

18:36.400 --> 18:40.820
♪ How I would hurt
if you would go ♪

18:40.820 --> 18:44.740
♪ Deeply ♪

18:44.740 --> 18:47.240
♪ Down inside of me ♪

18:50.250 --> 18:52.250
♪ Is our love forever ♪

18:52.250 --> 18:56.250
♪ Can anyone ever know? ♪

18:58.670 --> 19:01.560
♪ For all I remember ♪

19:01.560 --> 19:06.010
♪ I never have felt love so ♪

19:07.980 --> 19:10.900
♪ So deeply ♪

19:12.770 --> 19:15.770
♪ Deeply ♪

19:17.740 --> 19:19.780
♪ Deeply ♪

19:22.690 --> 19:25.580
♪ Deeply ♪

19:28.080 --> 19:31.590
♪ Our love is made by two ♪

19:31.590 --> 19:36.090
♪ And I can't make it
without you ♪

19:36.090 --> 19:38.090
♪ Deeply ♪

19:41.100 --> 19:42.600
♪ Deeply ♪

19:45.100 --> 19:48.100
♪ Deeply ♪

19:51.110 --> 19:53.110
♪ For our love ♪

19:56.110 --> 19:59.110
♪ For our love. ♪

20:01.120 --> 20:03.040
(music ends,
cheering, applause)

20:05.950 --> 20:07.370
Potsie,

20:07.370 --> 20:10.580
that's a beautiful song and
you did a wonderful job with it.

20:10.580 --> 20:12.330
Oh, thank you. Thank you!

20:16.250 --> 20:17.250
It was great!

20:17.250 --> 20:18.750
Great song!
Thanks.

20:18.750 --> 20:19.590
All right.

20:19.590 --> 20:20.890
All right,
this is it, Rich.

20:20.890 --> 20:22.390
After they play
"Good Night Sweetheart,"

20:22.390 --> 20:23.890
we all split
for the lake.

20:23.890 --> 20:25.260
Yeah.

20:25.260 --> 20:27.680
Clear. Excuse me.

20:27.680 --> 20:29.510
ARLENE:
Hey, what's Mr.
Connors doing here?

20:29.510 --> 20:31.310
I don't know,
but whenever Connors shows up,

20:31.310 --> 20:32.810
it's something bad.
Yeah.

20:32.810 --> 20:36.320
Yeah, the last surprise we had
was a fire drill in the rain.

20:36.320 --> 20:37.270
AL:
Attention.

20:37.270 --> 20:40.740
Vice Principal Connors
would like a few words with you.

20:40.740 --> 20:43.110
(band plays riff)

20:43.110 --> 20:46.500
Thank you, graduates,
and congratulations.

20:46.500 --> 20:49.500
However, I have just come
from looking at the final exams

20:49.500 --> 20:52.500
in Coach McMillan's
Health and Hygiene class.

20:52.500 --> 20:55.500
And I must say that
I am shocked to find out

20:55.500 --> 20:57.840
that this class
is nothing but a sham.

20:57.840 --> 21:00.210
(crowd murmurs)

21:00.210 --> 21:04.210
One genius thought that
a patella was a nickel cigar.

21:05.210 --> 21:07.720
Hey, he called
me a genius!

21:09.550 --> 21:13.360
I have taken the liberty
of regrading all the exams

21:13.360 --> 21:14.720
and everybody has flunked.

21:14.720 --> 21:16.610
(clamoring)

21:16.610 --> 21:17.480
Now, now,

21:17.480 --> 21:21.310
if any of you flunkees want to,

21:21.310 --> 21:23.820
want to graduate,
you may all-- it is open to

21:24.320 --> 21:26.820
all of these seniors--
you may take another exam

21:26.820 --> 21:28.790
tomorrow morning at 8:30 sharp.

21:28.790 --> 21:31.160
But if you don't pass,
you don't graduate.

21:31.160 --> 21:32.070
(murmurs)

21:32.070 --> 21:35.880
And now, you may go back
to having your fun.

21:35.880 --> 21:37.750
(clamoring)

21:42.250 --> 21:45.250
Some of the seniors may not
have heard my announcement,

21:45.250 --> 21:47.060
so please make sure
that they hear it.

21:47.060 --> 21:50.840
I understand that you're
very good at spreading the word.

21:54.350 --> 21:56.230
He flunked the
whole class!

21:56.230 --> 21:58.730
Big deal. I didn't like
Health and Hygiene anyway.

21:58.730 --> 22:01.190
Potsie, don't you realize
we're not graduating now?

22:01.570 --> 22:03.160
Oh, sure we will.

22:03.160 --> 22:06.020
We're all gonna study right
after we go watch the sunrise.

22:06.270 --> 22:07.360
Yeah.
Sunrise?

22:07.360 --> 22:08.860
Uh, we're not
watching any sunrise.

22:08.860 --> 22:10.200
We've got to go
to Kim's and study.

22:10.500 --> 22:11.580
Oh, yeah.

22:11.580 --> 22:13.580
I'll meet you up on
Blueberry Hill some other night.

22:14.080 --> 22:14.580
(groans)

22:15.000 --> 22:15.580
Bye.

22:16.080 --> 22:18.090
I'm sorry about
the bee sting.

22:18.090 --> 22:19.590
POTSIE:
Bye.
Bye.
Bye.

22:20.010 --> 22:21.540
No sunrise.

22:23.590 --> 22:26.600
Richard, we'll discuss
how this happened tomorrow.

22:26.600 --> 22:27.600
But right now,
I think you guys

22:28.100 --> 22:29.100
better go home
and start studying.

22:29.100 --> 22:30.600
Now, calm
down, Howard.

22:30.600 --> 22:34.050
We'll go home and we'll make
some coffee for the boys.

22:37.390 --> 22:38.470
I can't
believe this.

22:38.470 --> 22:39.980
Of all nights...
We're not
gonna graduate.

22:39.980 --> 22:41.480
We're gonna be stuck here
for another year.
(all chattering)

22:41.480 --> 22:42.360
What are we gonna do?
I don't...

22:42.610 --> 22:44.700
Stop moaning.

22:44.700 --> 22:46.530
You're gonna pass this test,
you're gonna graduate.

22:46.780 --> 22:48.870
Oh, come on, Fonz,
it's out of the question.

22:48.870 --> 22:50.290
The test is
tomorrow morning at 8:30.

22:50.620 --> 22:52.200
Let me tell you something,
I think you're forgetting

22:52.200 --> 22:53.710
that you got graduation,

22:53.710 --> 22:55.710
one of the most important
things in your life.

22:55.710 --> 22:57.210
You got your big five.

22:57.210 --> 22:58.160
You got life,
you got death,

22:58.710 --> 23:00.630
you got marriage,
you got graduation.

23:00.960 --> 23:03.050
Yeah, but, Fonz,
that's only four.

23:03.050 --> 23:04.380
What's number five?

23:04.580 --> 23:06.170
Heyyy.

23:06.170 --> 23:08.670
RALPH:
Oh, I like number five.

23:08.670 --> 23:10.170
Listen up.

23:10.170 --> 23:12.670
I want you at my place
in 20 minutes.

23:12.670 --> 23:14.560
You're gonna study your little
heads off, you understand?

23:14.810 --> 23:17.400
All right, you're gonna
graduate with me.

23:17.400 --> 23:19.900
I didn't go through night school
to graduate by myself, dig it?

23:19.900 --> 23:20.900
Right, Fonz.
Okay, Fonz.

23:20.900 --> 23:22.900
All right,
departez-vous.

23:23.320 --> 23:25.400
Yeah, okay, Fonz.
Yeah, okay, Fonz, yeah.

23:25.400 --> 23:27.410
Oh, shh.
What a night.

23:27.410 --> 23:30.410
We blew the sunrise, and now
we're not gonna graduate.

23:30.410 --> 23:31.410
It's worse
than that, Rich,

23:31.910 --> 23:34.410
We're gonna have to give back
our graduation presents.

23:34.410 --> 23:36.420
I didn't get any!

23:38.420 --> 23:40.500
Well, it's that time again.

23:40.500 --> 23:43.510
And time for the last dance
of the evening.

23:43.510 --> 23:46.510
And it's time for us to say,
in our own way...

23:48.960 --> 23:51.050
♪ Good night ♪
(band playing
"Good Night, Sweetheart")

23:51.050 --> 23:52.930
♪ Sweetheart ♪

23:54.270 --> 23:56.770
♪ Till we meet ♪

23:57.270 --> 24:00.220
♪ Tomorrow ♪

24:00.610 --> 24:04.190
(slowly):
You understand, this
is the last dance,

24:04.690 --> 24:08.610
then I have to go and
help my friends study.

24:08.950 --> 24:10.530
Dig it?

24:12.530 --> 24:13.490
(blows)

24:13.820 --> 24:16.400
They can start
without me.

24:18.910 --> 24:22.410
♪ Good night. ♪

24:30.420 --> 24:31.390
We're never gonna...

24:31.750 --> 24:33.310
You're gonna pass this test,

24:33.310 --> 24:34.840
and you're gonna graduate.

24:34.840 --> 24:37.260
I didn't go through night school
to graduate by my lonesome.

24:37.590 --> 24:41.010
"You will receive your
diploma in the mail."

24:41.430 --> 24:42.810
And I studied
my heart out.

24:43.010 --> 24:46.600
And now they want to send me
my diploma in the mail,

24:46.600 --> 24:48.400
like I was a "Dear Occupant."

24:48.650 --> 24:51.520
When I worry, I cook,
and when you worry, you eat.

24:53.690 --> 24:55.580
That's why we have
a happy marriage.

24:55.740 --> 24:58.330
And that's why
you have a happy tummy.

25:04.790 --> 25:07.340
♪ Good-bye, gray sky,
hello, blue ♪

25:07.340 --> 25:09.880
♪ There's nothing can hold me
when I hold you ♪

25:10.380 --> 25:12.380
♪ It feels so right,
it can't be wrong ♪

25:12.380 --> 25:15.380
♪ Rockin' and rollin'
all week long ♪

25:15.380 --> 25:17.220
♪ These days are ours ♪

25:20.550 --> 25:23.020
♪ These days are ours ♪

25:25.140 --> 25:37.600
♪ These happy days
are yours and mine ♪

